21 be included in such a report; and (3) characteristics for which certain performance
22 data must be disaggregated. (20 U.S.C. § 2323(b)(3)(C)) Existing law: (1)
23 authorizes the board of trustees of a school district or the governing body of a
24 charter school to offer a work-based learning program upon the approval of the
25 Superintendent of Public Instruction; and (2) requires a school district or charter
26 school that offers a work-based learning program to submit a report to the State
27 Board and the Legislature that contains certain information about the program,
28 including the number of participating pupils, disaggregated based on certain
29 characteristics. (NRS 389.167) Section 2 of this bill instead requires that the report
30 contain the information required to be included in the report submitted pursuant to
31 the Act, disaggregated according to the characteristics set forth in the Act.
